    "start": 0.0,
    "end": 14.3,
    "text": "She got down on hands and knees, one ear against the crowd"
  },
  {
    "start": 14.3,
    "end": 19.94,
    "text": "Holding her breath to hear something, but the dirt made not a sound tonight"
  },
  {
    "start": 19.94,
    "end": 33.38,
    "text": "Echoes as long as the lurk on distant foreign shores"
  },
  {
    "start": 33.38,
    "end": 37.92,
    "text": "Well, we dance just to please the gods, but only ask for more"
  },
  {
    "start": 37.92,
    "end": 43.72,
    "text": "And so it goes, but still we give ourselves to this"
  },
  {
    "start": 43.72,
    "end": 48.58,
    "text": "We can't spend our lives waiting to live"
  },
  {
    "start": 48.58,
    "end": 49.76,
    "text": "I'm calling"
  },
  {
    "start": 49.94,
    "end": 53.12,
    "text": "And I pray for dawn"
  },
  {
    "start": 53.12,
    "end": 57.5,
    "text": "The daylight isn't what she wants"
  },
  {
    "start": 57.5,
    "end": 62.06,
    "text": "The concrete calls my name again"
  },
  {
    "start": 62.06,
    "end": 68.96,
    "text": "A final lane through the cracks I slip"
  },
  {
    "start": 68.96,
    "end": 78.04,
    "text": "The postcard says, wish you a hell of a father"
  },
  {
    "start": 78.04,
    "end": 79.92,
    "text": "I was there holding her breath"
  },
  {
    "start": 79.94,
    "end": 83.12,
    "text": "I heard someone sobbing"
  },
  {
    "start": 83.12,
    "end": 85.7,
